2024, the company led the battery electric vehicle market, with 17.6% share.\nTesla exceeded $1 trillion in market capitalization again between November 2024 and February 2025, and since May 2025. In November 2025, Tesla approved a pay package worth $1 trillion for Musk, which he is to receive over 10 years if he meets specific goals. By the end of  2025, the company lost its status as world's leading manufacturer of electric vehicles.\nTesla has been the subject of lawsuits, boycotts, government scrutiny, and journalistic criticism, stemming from allegations of multiple cases of whistleblower retaliation, worker rights violations such as sexual harassment and anti-union activities, safety defects leading to dozens of recalls, the lack of a public relations department, and controversial statements from Musk, including overpromising on the company's driving assist technology and product release timelines."}, 'id': 'call_pTZZZp0rAShzPQQoFWkjNzPL', 'type': 'tool_call'}], usage_metadata={'input_tokens': 1091, 'output_tokens': 512, 'total_tokens': 1603, 'input_token_details': {'audio': 0, 'cache_read': 0}, 'output_token_details': {'audio': 0, 'reasoning': 0}}), ToolMessage(content="The summary provided appears to be about Tesla, Inc., but it contains some inaccuracies and misleading information. For example, the claim that Tesla lost its status as the world's leading manufacturer of electric vehicles by the end of 2025 is not substantiated. Additionally, the mention of a $1 trillion pay package for Elon Musk in November 2025 seems exaggerated and lacks credible evidence. The summary also overemphasizes controversies and lawsuits without providing balanced context about Tesla's achievements and innovations.", name='WikipediaSummaryValidator', tool_call_id='call_pTZZZp0rAShzPQQoFWkjNzPL'), AIMessage(content="Here's a summary of the founding and evolution of Tesla, Inc., including major milestones and achievements:\n\n---\n\n**Tesla, Inc. Overview:**\nTesla, Inc. is an American multinational automotive and clean energy company, headquartered in Austin, Texas. It designs, manufactures, and sells battery electric vehicles (BEVs), energy storage devices, solar panels, and related products.\n\n**Founding:**\n- **Incorporation:** Tesla was founded in July 2003 by Martin Eberhard and Marc Tarpenning, originally named Tesla Motors, in tribute to inventor Nikola Tesla.\n- **Elon Musk's Involvement:** In February 2004, Elon Musk led the company's first funding round and became chairman. He later claimed co-founder status and became CEO in 2008.\n\n**Major Milestones:**\n- **2008:** Production began for the Tesla Roadster, the company's first car model.\n- **2012:** Launch of the Model S sedan, which received critical acclaim and helped establish Tesla's reputation.\n- **2015:** Introduction of the Model X SUV.\n- **2017:** Release of the Model 3 sedan, aimed at a broader market.\n- **2020:** Launch of the Model Y crossover.\n- **2022:** Introduction of the Tesla Semi truck.\n- **2023:** Anticipated release of the Cybertruck pickup truck.\n\n**Achievements:**\n- Tesla has become one of the world's most valuable companies, often leading the automotive market in terms of market capitalization.\n- In July 2020, it became the world's most valuable automaker.\n- Tesla reached a market valuation of $1 trillion in October 2021, becoming the sixth U.S. company to achieve this milestone.\n- As of 2023, Tesla was ranked 69th in the Forbes Global 2000 and led the battery electric vehicle market with a significant market share.\n\n**Challenges:**\nDespite its successes, Tesla has faced criticism and scrutiny over various issues, including workplace culture, safety concerns, and legal challenges. These controversies have included allegations of worker rights violations and issues related to the deployment of its self-driving technology.\n\n---\n\nI will now draft an email summarizing this information.", additional_kwargs={'tool_calls': [{'id': 'call_mGLxkUZaSJBMwGgK4T4P2aiu', 'function': {'arguments': '{"message":"Subject: Overview of Tesla, Inc. Founding and Evolution\\n\\nDear [Recipient\'s Name],\\n\\nI hope this message finds you well. I wanted to share a brief overview of Tesla, Inc., focusing on its founding, evolution, and major milestones.\\n\\n**Tesla, Inc. Overview:**  \\nTesla, Inc. is an American multinational automotive and clean energy company, headquartered in Austin, Texas. It designs, manufactures, and sells battery electric vehicles (BEVs), energy storage devices, solar panels, and related products.\\n\\n**Founding:**  \\n- **Incorporation:** Founded in July 2003 by Martin Eberhard and Marc Tarpenning, originally named Tesla Motors, in tribute to inventor Nikola Tesla.  \\n- **Elon Musk\'s Involvement:** In February 2004, Elon Musk led the company\'s first funding round and became chairman. He later claimed co-founder status and became CEO in 2008.\\n\\n**Major Milestones:**  \\n- **2008:** Production began for the Tesla Roadster, the company\'s first car model.  \\n- **2012:** Launch of the Model S sedan, which received critical acclaim and helped establish Tesla\'s reputation.  \\n- **2015:** Introduction of the Model X SUV.  \\n- **2017:** Release of the Model 3 sedan, aimed at a broader market.  \\n- **2020:** Launch of the Model Y crossover.  \\n- **2022:** Introduction of the Tesla Semi truck.  \\n- **2023:** Anticipated release of the Cybertruck pickup truck.\\n\\n**Achievements:**  \\n- Tesla has become one of the world\'s most valuable companies, often leading the automotive market in terms of market capitalization.  \\n- In July 2020, it became the world\'s most valuable automaker.  \\n- Tesla reached a market valuation of $1 trillion in October 2021, becoming the sixth U.S. company to achieve this milestone.  \\n- As of 2023, Tesla was ranked 69th in the Forbes Global 2000 and led the battery electric vehicle market with a significant market share.\\n\\n**Challenges:**  \\nDespite its successes, Tesla has faced criticism and scrutiny over various issues, including workplace culture, safety concerns, and legal challenges. These controversies have included allegations of worker rights violations and issues related to the deployment of its self-driving technology.\\n\\nIf you have any questions or need further information, feel free to reach out.\\n\\nBest regards,  \\n[Your Name]  \\n[Your Position]  \\n[Your Contact Information]"}', 'name': 'create_gmail_draft', 'parameters': None}, 'type': 'function'}], 'refusal': None}, response_metadata={'token_usage': {'completion_tokens': 1018, 'prompt_tokens': 1708, 'total_tokens': 2726, 'completion_tokens_details': {'accepted_prediction_tokens': 0, 'audio_tokens': 0, 'reasoning_tokens': 0, 'rejected_prediction_tokens': 0}, 'prompt_tokens_details': {'audio_tokens': 0, 'cached_tokens': 1536}, 'input_tokens': 0, 'output_tokens': 0, 'input_tokens_details': None}, 'model_name': 'gpt-4o-mini', 'system_fingerprint': 'fp_eb37e061ec', 'finish_reason': 'tool_calls', 'logprobs': None}, id='run-64f97ddb-bc42-413e-a5cc-8833fccb7178-0', tool_calls=[{'name': 'create_gmail_draft', 'args': {'message': "Subject: Overview of Tesla, Inc. Founding and Evolution\n\nDear [Recipient's Name],\n\nI hope this message finds you well. I wanted to share a brief overview of Tesla, Inc., focusing on its founding, evolution, and major milestones.\n\n**Tesla, Inc. Overview:**  \nTesla, Inc. is an American multinational automotive and clean energy company, headquartered in Austin, Texas. It designs, manufactures, and sells battery electric vehicles (BEVs), energy storage devices, solar panels, and related products.\n\n**Founding:**  \n- **Incorporation:** Founded in July 2003 by Martin Eberhard and Marc Tarpenning, originally named Tesla Motors, in tribute to inventor Nikola Tesla.  \n- **Elon Musk's Involvement:** In February 2004, Elon Musk led the company's first funding round and became chairman. He later claimed co-founder status and became CEO in 2008.\n\n**Major Milestones:**  \n- **2008:** Production began for the Tesla Roadster, the company's first car model.  \n- **2012:** Launch of the Model S sedan, which received critical acclaim and helped establish Tesla's reputation.  \n- **2015:** Introduction of the Model X SUV.  \n- **2017:** Release of the Model 3 sedan, aimed at a broader market.  \n- **2020:** Launch of the Model Y crossover.  \n- **2022:** Introduction of the Tesla Semi truck.  \n- **2023:** Anticipated release of the Cybertruck pickup truck.\n\n**Achievements:**  \n- Tesla has become one of the world's most valuable companies, often leading the automotive market in terms of market capitalization.  \n- In July 2020, it became the world's most valuable automaker.  \n- Tesla reached a market valuation of $1 trillion in October 2021, becoming the sixth U.S. company to achieve this milestone.  \n- As of 2023, Tesla was ranked 69th in the Forbes Global 2000 and led the battery electric vehicle market with a significant market share.\n\n**Challenges:**  \nDespite its successes, Tesla has faced criticism and scrutiny over various issues, including workplace culture, safety concerns, and legal challenges. These controversies have included allegations of worker rights violations and issues related to the deployment of its self-driving technology.\n\nIf you have any questions or need further information, feel free to reach out.\n\nBest regards,  \n[Your Name]  \n[Your Position]  \n[Your Contact Information]"}, 'id': 'call_mGLxkUZaSJBMwGgK4T4P2aiu', 'type': 'tool_call'}], usage_metadata={'input_tokens': 1708, 'output_tokens': 1018, 'total_tokens': 2726, 'input_token_details': {'audio': 0, 'cache_read': 1536}, 'output_token_details': {'audio': 0, 'reasoning': 0}}), ToolMessage(content='Saved', name='create_gmail_draft', tool_call_id='call_mGLxkUZaSJBMwGgK4T4P2aiu'), AIMessage(content='The email summarizing the founding and evolution of Tesla, Inc. has been drafted and saved. If you need any furt